# set a variable that will call whatever column we want to visualise on the map
variable = "Count"
# set the range for the choropleth
vmin, vmax = 0, 100
# create figure and axes for Matplotlib
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, figsize=(10, 6),linewidth=1,edgecolor='black')

merged.plot(column=variable, cmap="BuGn", linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor="0.1")

# remove the axis
ax.axis("off")
# add a title
#ax.set_title("Distribution of Flat Offers", fontdict={"fontsize": "12", "fontweight" : "3"})


# Create colorbar as a legend
sm = plt.cm.ScalarMappable(cmap="BuGn", norm=plt.Normalize(vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax))
# empty array for the data range
sm._A = []
# add the colorbar to the figure
cbar = fig.colorbar(sm,ax=plt.gca())

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('verteilung.png', edgecolor= 'black')

import datetime
# Set a list to filter out the dates

filters = (['nach Vereinbarung','sofort','kurzfristig','vermietet','nach Fertigstellung','nach Verkauf',
                'nach Kaufpreiszahlung', 'in Planung', 'nach Beurkundung', 'mittelfristig' ])


# Extract the avaliability dates

datet = list()

for i in dataset[(dataset['VERfÜGBAR AB'].isnull() == False)].index:
    
    y= re.search(r"^\b(\d{2})\b.\b(\d{2})\b.\b(\d{4})\b$", dataset.loc[dataset.index == i, 'VERfÜGBAR AB'].item())
    if y!= None:
        x = dataset.loc[dataset.index == i, 'VERfÜGBAR AB'].item()
        x = x.replace('.','/')
        x = x.replace('-','/')
        #print(x)
        x = pd.to_datetime(x,format = '%d/%m/%Y')
        dataset.loc[dataset.index == i, 'VERfÜGBAR AB'] = x
        datet.append(i)
        
 # Filter the dataframe
dates = dataset[(dataset['VERfÜGBAR AB'].isnull() == False) & (~dataset['VERfÜGBAR AB'].isin(filters))]['VERfÜGBAR AB']

dates= pd.to_datetime(dates)
